4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi","html_url":"https://github.com/timfi","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-06-08T14:38:25Z","updated_at":"2020-06-08T14:38:53Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"Yeah I saw that issue and was wondering to myself if I should simply give my two cents there, but I think the nicest way to handle this would be expose this functionality to the user and then simply also use it for the pager.\r\n\r\nAdditionally I just did some digging, trying to find out if something like this could work on windows. (Obviously my implementation above does not due to the use of *nix commands to find out the control sequencesâ€¦) And it turns out their Windows Console actually support at least the important sequences, at least according to their [docs]( https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/console/console-virtual-terminal-sequences#alternate-screen-buffer).","performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/comments/640750842","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan/rich/issues/103#issuecomment-640750842","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/103","id":640750842,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY0MDc1MDg0Mg==","user":{"login":"timfi","id":30415153,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMwNDE1MTUz","avatar_url":"https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/30415153?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi","html_url":"https://github.com/timfi","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timfi/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-06-08T16:58:14Z","updated_at":"2020-06-08T17:01:56Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"I was wondering how some other project (though in other languages) achieve a similar effect in terminals that don't support ANSI escape sequences and stumbled upon a [version of `less` that works on windows](https://github.com/adoxa/less/). They seem to either [create a new `ConsoleScreenBuffer` using `windows.h`](https://github.com/adoxa/less/blob/master/screen.c#L1491-L1529) or [simply print new lines until the screen is full](https://github.com/adoxa/less/blob/master/screen.c#L1589-L1612).\r\n\r\nPS: @willmcgugan I'm looking further into this on my own volition with no strings attached. I'm simply curious myself atm and thought that you might find some of the things I find use since have to some lengths to make `rich` as cross-platform as possible. :+1: \r\n","performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/comments/641169490","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan/rich/issues/103#issuecomment-641169490","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/103","id":641169490,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY0MTE2OTQ5MA==","user":{"login":"willmcgugan","id":55